info.description:
# ouva-protos

A helper library containing all Protobuf messages used in Kafka, gRPC & Redis.

## How to Build

```shell
# Update version if necessary by running this command:
# make set-version VERSION=<NEW_VERSION>
make build
```

## How to Release

Release process means the library passed all its tests & ready to be deployed on both PyPi and Maven registries. We use [semantic versioning](https://semver.org/) for each release so keep that in mind while setting a new version.

```shell
make release NEXUS_USER=<YOUR_NEXUS_USERNAME> NEXUS_PWD=<YOUR_NEXUS_PASSWORD> VERSION=<NEW_VERSION>
```

## How to Generate Proto Descriptor File

```shell
make generate-proto-desc
```

## Messages

### Commands

* **attribute**: Attribute detection command
* **change_room_state**: Enables/disables a room with sensor when a patient is admitted to a room (or a patient left a room after discharge)

### Events

* **frame**: Frame events with person crops
* **notification**: (info, warning or alert level) notification events or cancellation events.
* **patient-risk**: Published only when a risk flag (fall risk, wander risk, etc.) of any patient changes.
* **patient-session**: Patient session or standby events.
* **patient-status**: Patient status events regarding latest patient action in the room.
* **person-count**: Published only when person counts in a room change.
* **person-metadata**: Person metadata event containing all pose data & related person counts.
* **room-metadata**: Persisted in Redis with up-to-date sensor metadata only when related data changes or on service startups.
* **room-status**: Room status events regarding patient ADT actions.
* **segment-metadata**: Segmentation metadata events regarding room objects (chair, bed, etc.)
* **timeline**: Timeline events that provides historical data of a patient or room.
